<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-09T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-09T01:00:00-05:00" n="127" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No, 893.00/2687</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-09T14:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 9, 1917, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Consul General at Canton reports efforts to set up provisional Government
                            Canton not likely to have much success. Chances I believe preservation
                            national unity are better, but even if separate provisional Government
                            should be formed I have reason to believe it will probably also declare
                            war against Germany in order to avoid international complications. This
                            would form the basis of compromise. At all times have sought to impress
                            upon leaders political parties the policy of your note June 4.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>